JavaScript, on the other hand, is a programming language that is used to create interactive and dynamic effects on a website. It is used to add functionality to a website, such as animations, pop-up windows, and form validation. JavaScript is a dynamic language, meaning that it can manipulate the content of a website and respond to user interactions.

